Cognizant® API Proxy Migrator for Kong (AKA Apigee to Kong Maker)

This automation tool migrates Apigee proxies to their equivalent Kong proxies, including the most commonly used Apigee policies.

What can you achieve with this tool?

Accelerate time to market: The automated migration of Apigee proxies to Kong through this tool ensures faster product delivery.

Reduce delivery effort: The tool automates the API migration lifecycle, enabling API promotion in minutes with minimal rework.

Ensure code quality standards: Enforce centralized policies and organizational defaults to maintain code quality.

Simplify developer tasks: Developers only need to know where to place Apigee proxy bundles, without requiring knowledge of Kong Gateway.

What Apigee Policies can be migrated to Kong Plugins?

This is the list of Apigee policies that can be migrated using this automation tool, along with the API proxy configuration. Some policies are currently marked as 'In Progress' or 'TBD,' indicating that their migration logic is still being developed.

Sr.No Apigee Policy Name Description Kong Equivalent Plugin Migration Status 1 Quota Controls the number of requests allowed within a time interval. Rate Limiting, Request Size Limiting Completed 2 Spike Arrest Prevents sudden bursts of traffic. Potentially custom plugin Completed (in enhancecment as per latest change in Kong release) 3 AccessControl Allows or denies access based on IP addresses. IP Restriction Completed 4 Verify API Key Authenticates requests using an API key. Key Authentication Completed 5 Basic Authentication Authenticates requests using username/password. Basic Authentication Completed 6 OAuth v2.0 Implements the OAuth 2.0 authorization framework. OAuth 2.0 Authentication Completed 7 JSON Threat Protection Protects against JSON-based attacks. JSON Threat Protection In Progress 8 XML Threat Protection Protects against XML-based attacks. XML Threat Protection In Progress 9 JWT Generates, verifies, or decodes JSON Web Tokens (JWTs). JWT In Progress 10 Assign Message Creates or modifies request/response messages. Request Transformer, Response Transformer In Progress 11 XML to JSON Converts XML payloads to JSON. XML to JSON In Progress 12 JSON to XML Converts JSON payloads to XML. JSON to XML In Progress 13 SAML Assertion Generates or validates SAML assertions. Potentially custom plugin TBD 14 Extract Variables Extracts data from requests/responses (headers, payloads, etc.). Request Transformer TBD 15 Service Callout Sends a request to an external service. Request Transformer, Potentially custom plugin TBD 16 Raise Fault Raises a custom error response. Potentially custom plugin TBD 17 Caching policies (Populate/Lookup/Invalidate Cache) Store and retrieve data for faster response Potentially custom plugin TBD 18 Message Logging Logs request/response information. File Log, TCP Log, HTTP Log or Potentially custom plugin TBD 19 Regular Expression Protection Protects against regular expression-based attacks. Request/Response Header or Potentially custom plugin TBD 20 XSL Transform Transforms XML payloads using XSLT. Potentially custom plugin TBD
